article.headline: Mount St. Mary's 69, St. Francis (Pa.) 58
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Shivaughn Wiggins scored 22 points to lead Mount St. Mary's to a 69-58 victory over St. Francis (Pa.) in a Northeast Conference game on Saturday night. Raven Barber added 12 points and Rashad Whack 11 for the Mountaineers (10-13, 5-7), who have won three of their past four games. Ben Millaud-Meunier led St. Francis (2-21, 2-10) with 15 points, Anthony Ervin scored 12 and Earl Brown had 10. The Red Flash has lost two in a row and 10 of their past 11. Trailing 7-6 5:03 into the game, the Mountaineers ran off 15 consecutive points to lead 21-7 with 6:45 left on two free throws from Wiggins. Mount St. Mary's, which has won six in a row and 14 of the past 15 in the series, led 32-18 at the half and was never threatened. The closest the Red Flash got in the second half was 10 points.
